📘 Product Requirement Document (PRD)
Quizo – Smart Quiz Platform (Simplified Version)
1. 📌 Introduction
1.1 Purpose

Quizo is a web-based quiz management platform designed to simplify the process of creating, attempting, and evaluating quizzes in an academic environment.

This document defines the product requirements, core features, and system behavior of Quizo. It is intended for developers, project evaluators, and academic supervisors to understand the scope and functionality of the system.

The platform focuses on delivering a streamlined and efficient quiz experience while maintaining essential features such as role-based access, automated evaluation, and real-time results.

1.2 Product Overview

Quizo is a lightweight and user-friendly application that enables:

Teachers to create and manage quizzes
Students to attempt quizzes within a time limit
System to automatically evaluate responses and generate results

The system eliminates the need for manual quiz checking by providing instant feedback and structured quiz management.

Unlike complex learning systems, Quizo is designed to be focused, fast, and easy to use, making it ideal for academic projects and small-scale deployments.

1.3 Scope

The scope of Quizo includes the following core functionalities:

User authentication (Teacher and Student roles)
Quiz creation with multiple-choice questions (MCQs)
Timed quiz participation
Automatic answer evaluation
Instant result generation

The system does not include complex administrative workflows or advanced analytics, ensuring a clean and maintainable design while preserving essential functionality.

1.4 Key Objectives

The main objectives of Quizo are:

To provide a simple and efficient platform for conducting quizzes
To automate the evaluation process and reduce manual effort
To ensure fair and controlled quiz attempts using timers and attempt restrictions
To deliver a responsive and user-friendly interface
To demonstrate core software engineering principles such as role-based access and database-driven design
1.5 Target Users

Quizo is designed for the following users:

Teachers
Create quizzes
Add questions and correct answers
View student results
Students
Attempt quizzes
View scores and performance
1.6 Product Vision

The vision of Quizo is to provide a minimal yet powerful quiz platform that balances simplicity with functionality.

Instead of focusing on unnecessary complexity, the system emphasizes:

clarity in design
efficiency in performance
ease of use

This makes Quizo a practical solution for academic environments and a strong demonstration of full-stack development skills.

1.7 Key Features (High-Level)
Role-based login system
Quiz creation and management
Randomized question order
Timed quiz attempts with auto-submit
Automatic MCQ evaluation
Instant result display
1.8 Design Philosophy

Quizo follows a “Keep It Simple, Yet Effective” approach:

Minimal steps for users
Clean and intuitive UI
Focus on core functionality over feature overload

This ensures faster development, better maintainability, and a smoother user experience.